cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes an ensemble-based approach for online machine learning. It also involves learning Naive Bayes classifiers and projecting the original training set to lower dimensional space, which are common techniques in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS) as it involves learning sequences of data and generating training sets. The sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV) are less likely but still possible as the proposed approach may have applications in these areas.
